{
  "analysis": "The terminal is still flooded by output from the earlier `findexact` brute-force process. We must regain a stable shell before any diagnostics or encoder fixes. The known-good evidence is that `4f 02` decompresses to `01`, while our generated non-empty streams are invalid. After stabilization, clean `decsim` diagnostics comparing `4f 02` versus `/app/t1.comp` are needed to identify the arithmetic encoder bug.",
  "plan": "Send multiple Ctrl-C interrupts, then run a robust kill loop that repeatedly kills any `findexact`/`brute3` processes by PID until none remain. Wait briefly and print `STABLE`, `CLEANED`, and `PROMPT_READY` markers. Do not run diagnostics in this batch to avoid further interleaving.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "C-c\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "C-c\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "C-c\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "for i in 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8; do pids=$(pgrep -f 'findexact|brute3'); if [ -z \"$pids\" ]; then echo NONE; break; fi; kill -9 $pids 2>/dev/null; sleep 0.3; done; echo STABLE\n",
      "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "pgrep -af 'findexact|brute3' || echo CLEANED\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo PROMPT_READY\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ]
}
